revision.text:
An '''amniocyte''' (literally "lamb cell") is a [[cell (biology)|cell]] of a [[fetus]] which is suspended in the [[amniotic fluid]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Freshney|first1=R. Ian|title=Culture of animal cells : a manual of basic technique and specialized applications|date=2010|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell|location=Hoboken, N.J.|isbn=9780470528129|edition=6th}}</ref>

